&sect; XX. Un&s;ucce&s;sful attempt upon Toulon. &sect; XXI.
Sir Cloude&s;ley Shovel wrecked on the rocks of Scilly. Weak|ne&s;s
of the Emperor on the Upper Rhine. &sect; XXII. Inter|view
between the King of Sweden and the Duke of Marl|borough.
&sect; XXIII. Inactive campaign in the Nether|lands.
&sect; XXIV. Harley begins to form a party again&s;t
the Duke of Marlborough. &sect; XXV. The nation di&s;|contented
with the Whig mini&s;try. &sect; XXVI. Meeting
of the fir&s;t Briti&s;h parliament. &sect; XXVII. Enquiry into
the &s;tate of the war in Spain. &sect; XXVIII. Gregg, a clerk
in the &s;ecretary's office, detected in a corre&s;pondence with the
French mini&s;try. &sect; XXIX. Harley re&s;igns his employ|ment.
&sect; XXX. The Pretender embarks at Dunkirk for
Scotland. &sect; XXXI. His de&s;ign is defeated. &sect; XXXII.
