and Bruges. &sect; XXXV. They are routed at Oudenarde.
&sect; XXXVI. The allies inve&s;t Li&s;le. &sect; XXXVII. They
defeat a large body of French forces at Wynendale. The
Elector of Bavaria attacks Bru&s;&s;els. &sect; XXXVIII. Li&s;le
&s;urrendered, Ghent taken, and Bruges abandoned. &sect; XXXIX.
Conque&s;t of Minorca by General Stanhope. XL. Rup|ture
between the Pope and the Emperor. &sect; XLI. Death of
